rComments: She is definitly a nice and pleasent person to have as a proffesor but she is also one of the toughest graders i have ever encountered. You can reach her in office hours but sometimes it isn't clear at the end on how exactly you can improve yourself to her liking for better marks. Overall however, i would recommend taking her courses.

I've taken multiple courses with Nefsky and in every case she has been very enthusiastic and carrying for her students. There are weekly assignments but they are small and give easy marks if you actually complete them. She really loves students coming to her office hours and its really worth the visit. She gives amazing feed back!

She has the cute quirky philosophy prof dynamic down. Always open to students ideas on the course material and lets it drive the direction of lectures while tying into material. Worksheets provided that summarize lecture materials which makes studying easy. Currently hunting for another philo course to take with her so that says something.
